Festus Keyamo, Nigeria’s Minister of State for Labour and Employment, has described the All Progressives Congress, APC, as a national party. Keyamo was reacting to the decision of APC Northern governors to root for a Southern president He noted that APC governors have displayed statesmanship and are committed to Nigeria by their decision. In a tweet, Keyamo said this is one of the most important moments in Nigeria’s history. He wrote: “A truly national Party has come to stay. Whilst others hope to cash in on ethnic sentiments to win AT ALL COST, the Northern APC Govs have displayed statesmanship & commitment to the Nigerian Project. “Take note: this is one of the most pivotal moments in the history of Nigeria!” DAILY POST reported that APC Northern governors backed a Nigerian President of Southern extraction. 11 Northern governors urged President Muhammadu Buhari to consider a Southerner as his likely successor. The governors issued a statement to this effect after a meeting on Saturday. In the statement, they urged Northern presidential aspirants to withdraw from the race in the interest of the nation..